  <section id="about" class="section">
    <h2>Why Ethical AI Matters</h2>
    <p>AI technologies have immense potential—but with great power comes great responsibility. Ethical AI ensures fairness, transparency, and accountability in how we design and use AI tools.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="problems" class="section dark">
    <h2>Unethical Uses of AI</h2>
    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Deepfakes & Misinformation</h3>
        <p>AI-generated media can manipulate truth and deceive the public.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>AI Bias</h3>
        <p>Unchecked algorithms can reinforce racial, gender, or socioeconomic discrimination.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Privacy Violations</h3>
        <p>AI-powered surveillance may infringe on human rights and data privacy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Automated Plagiarism</h3>
        <p>Generative AI can be misused for mass production of fake, copied content.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="solutions" class="section">
    <h2>How We Can Prevent It</h2>
    <ul class="solution-list">
      <li><strong>Transparent AI:</strong> Promote openness in how AI models work.</li>
      <li><strong>Ethical Guidelines:</strong> Develop global frameworks for AI development.</li>
      <li><strong>Human Oversight:</strong> Ensure AI decisions are reviewed by people.</li>
      <li><strong>Public Awareness:</strong> Educate users and developers on responsible use.</li>
      <li><strong>Fair Regulation:</strong> Advocate for legal and policy frameworks to limit misuse.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="cta" id="contact">
